12. qui crucis nos religiosos putat. 2. Worship of the Cross. Cp. ad Nat. i. 12 3 Min. Fel. 29. The great reverence ever felt by Chris- tians for the symbol of salvation easily lent itself to the misconception of the heathen, who imagined that the material cross was to the Chris- tians what their own idols were to themselves. Tertullian contents himself with a conditional tu quoque ; Minucius Felix l. e. is more direct: ‘ cruces etiam nec colimus nec optamus.'
